Description: Colorado School of Paramedical Esthetics is a school in Denver.
Full Description: Colorado School of Paramedical Esthetics offers professional training in esthetics and massage therapy and is located in the beautiful and lively city of Denver, Colorado. Colorado School of Paramedical Esthetics believes hands-on training is the best education to prepare future professionals in the field. In order to receive a dual certificate in both esthetics and massage, students are required to take 700 hours of training in massage, and 600 hours of training in esthetics. Though the massage certificate is fairly new to the school, instructors and staff believe a dual certificate creates the most marketable professional. Esthetics courses include training in skin analysis, manual and mechanical facials, skin disorders, anatomy, physiology, hair removal, hydrotherapy, nutrition, advanced acne treatments, and much more. Students learn techniques, how to use machines and how to conduct evaluations. Massage courses involve massage techniques, swedish massage, therapeutic massage, sanitation and safety, body techniques, hot rock therapy, business practices and more. Students leave Colorado School of Paramedical Esthetics with the professional skills and business confidence to find a job in their field.
